Bob, if you wanted to, and also wanted to be crafty for fording applications,
a syncro snorkel goes right up the passenger side pillar to where the air is
certainly cold (depending on ambient obviously) though as Jamie mentions, you
are always getting ram and venturi effect in those scoops at speed.  Syncro
unit also has the little dust/water prefilter etc.  One could probably figure
a fairly easy way to plumb it given enough slicone turbo connectors from your
favorite auction site.
 
http://www.thesamba.com/vw/classifieds/detail.php?id=1243735
 
is an example. 
Price probably isn't terrible, though shipping might be a bit due to
cumbersome size.
 
