Bob Pratt writes:
> Has
anyone thought about installing a cold air intake system on a type 2 or
> type
1 engine? If so, how?
> Owned by a '78 Champagne Edition Westy and a '73 SB
Sunny

Bob
the late bay body has a cold air intake built in.
the air scoops in
the body of the late bay have a venturi effect to them.. as they have a narrow
area.. that increases the speed of the air flowing thru there, and drops the
air temps.
this reduced air temps is fed into the intake, as well as the
cooling fan.
neat engineering eh?
